fects 69 % of adults with spinal cord injury (SCI) and responds poorly to current treatments. Emerging evidence suggests that impaired mental body representations (MBR) may contribute to neuropathic pain. We aimed to identify changes in neuropathic pain, and sensorimotor function after Cognitive Multisensory Rehabilitation (CMR), a physical therapy which improves MBR, vs usual care. In this Phase I randomized delayed-treatment trial, 26 adults with SCI-related neuropathic pain were randomized to either 6 weeks of immediate CMR (group A), with 6-week+1-year follow-up; or a 6-week observational period+6-week CMR+1-year follow-up (Group B). We assessed neuropathic pain intensity, sensorimotor function, and SCI-related outcome measures.\u003c/p\u003e\n","funders":[{"organization":"University of Minnesota Medical School","identifierType":"ror","identifier":"https://ror.org/04jnprq39","awardNumber":"AIRP2-IND-30","awardDescription":"Academic Investment Research Program (AIRP)","awardTitle":""},{"organization":"National Center for Advancing Translational Sciences","identifierType":"ror","identifier":"https://ror.org/04pw6fb54","awardNumber":"5UL1TR002494-05","awardURI":"https://reporter.nih.gov/project-details/10366062","awardDescription":"","awardTitle":"University of Minnesota Clinical and TranslationalmScience Institute (UMN CTSI)"},{"organization":"National Institute of Biomedical Imaging and Bioengineering","identifierType":"ror","identifier":"https://ror.org/00372qc85","awardNumber":"5P41EB015894-25","awardURI":"https://reporter.nih.gov/project-details/9297304","awardDescription":"","awardTitle":"NMR Imaging and Spectroscopy"},{"organization":"National Institute of Neurological Disorders and Stroke","identifierType":"ror","identifier":"https://ror.org/01s5ya894","awardNumber":"5P30NS076408-09","awardURI":"https://reporter.nih.gov/project-details/10005498","awardDescription":"Institutional Center Core Grants to Support Neuroscience Research","awardTitle":"Core 1 - Acq